---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Driftless Logic - Built by Someone Who Lived It">
  <Header />

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative pt-20 pb-20 overflow-hidden bg-white">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-topo-pattern pointer-events-none opacity-100"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[500px] h-[500px] bg-primary/10 rounded-full blur-[100px] pointer-events-none mix-blend-multiply"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 flex flex-col items-center text-center">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 px-3 py-1 mb-8 shadow-sm">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-sm">person</span>
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-600">About</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-gray-900 mb-6">
          Built by someone who<span class="text-primary block mt-2">lived it.</span>
        </h1>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          Driftless Logic was founded by Jake Zebell—Navy veteran, former USDA executive, and 20-year federal IT leader who managed agile at a scale most people only read about.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder Story -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50 border-y border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Founder Story</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600 space-y-4">
          <p>
            I spent 14 years at USDA, the last several as a GS-15 leading 550 staff across 5 agile release trains. I ran PI planning for teams spread across the country. I watched talented developers burn hours in estimation sessions that predicted nothing. I saw critical work blocked for weeks because it didn't fit the sprint boundary.
          </p>
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900">
            I didn't leave because agile failed. I left because I saw what's coming next—and I wanted to build it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Credentials -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Credentials</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-xl">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="size-12 rounded-lg bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-primary">
              <span class="material-symbols-outlined">military_tech</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Military Service</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500">Navy veteran. Service-connected disability qualifies Driftless Logic as a Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business (SDVOSB).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-xl">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="size-12 rounded-lg bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-primary">
              <span class="material-symbols-outlined">account_balance</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Federal Leadership</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500">GS-15 at USDA Farm Production and Conservation. Managed enterprise-scale software delivery for programs that touch every farmer in America.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-xl">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="size-12 rounded-lg bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-primary">
              <span class="material-symbols-outlined">emoji_events</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Recognition</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500">USDA Abraham Lincoln Honor Award recipient—the department's highest recognition for exceptional service.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-xl">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="size-12 rounded-lg bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-primary">
              <span class="material-symbols-outlined">verified</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Certifications</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500">SAFe 6.0 SPC (Scaled Program Consultant). PMP. The credentials that prove I understand what we're evolving beyond.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Company -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-background-alt relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-topo-pattern opacity-40 pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Company</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600 space-y-4">
          <p>
            Driftless Logic LLC is a Wisconsin-based small business pursuing federal contracting opportunities. We're SDVOSB-qualified and currently completing SAM.gov registration and VetCert certification.
          </p>
          <p>
            The name comes from the <strong class="text-gray-900">Driftless Region</strong>—a unique geological area that glaciers never flattened. While everything around it was homogenized, the Driftless retained its natural complexity and diversity.
          </p>
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900">
            That's the philosophy behind our methodology: development that follows natural patterns, not imposed uniformity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-white border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Interested in partnership or licensing?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Or just want to have a conversation about where software development is headed? I'd like to hear from you.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-primary px-8 py-4 text-base font-bold text-black hover:bg-green-400 transition-all shadow-lg shadow-primary/30">
        Get in Touch
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[20px]">arrow_forward</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
